Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Senior Software Backend Engineer (Software Engineer III)* role with *TomoCredit*. I bring over three years of professional experience building backend systems, robust APIs, asynchronous workflow platforms, and cloud-based services, along with a strong academic foundation through my Master of Science in Computer Science at Pace University.

My recent work at Sperse closely matches the backend ownership this role requires. I took end-to-end ownership of backend projects for a multi-agent CRM platform using JavaScript, TypeScript, Node.js service patterns, Python, and FastAPI, delivering robust APIs that served 10,000+ users across 40+ specialized sub-agents with secure access control. I also built a React Flow and TypeScript workflow platform that handled asynchronous processes through durable Temporal execution, messaging queues, and Redis progress tracking, and created a FastMCP server exposing 160+ backend actions with RESTful patterns, GraphQL APIs schemas, tenant-aware access control, and built-in monitoring. To keep releases dependable, I built GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines with OpenTelemetry trace-based QA testing that flagged latency, accuracy, safety, and release-quality regressions before production.

At Qualitest, I built the kind of SQL, API, and AWS foundation TomoCredit needs for financial products that must be scalable and dependable. I designed, built, and maintained a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in Java and Spring Boot with SQL databases, Postgres, PostgreSQL, and Redis, delivering RESTful file APIs across S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO through expiring signed URLs. I also leveraged AWS services including EC2, EBS, RDS, Lambda, CloudWatch, Step Functions, and S3 to create cloud-based solutions, troubleshoot complex technical issues, and improve error recovery across 100K+ weekly executions. My PostgreSQL optimization work with window functions, materialized views, and indexes improved scalability for high performance reporting and exposed the data through React visualizations for product and business stakeholders.

TomoCredit's mission to replace the outdated credit system, open access to banking, and build a more inclusive credit system for people historically excluded from traditional credit models is exactly the kind of product impact I want to help own. I am also drawn to the team's emphasis on rigor, organization, discipline, and creative problem-solving, because that is how I approach engineering work: clear API contracts, traceable QA testing, production monitoring, and pragmatic collaboration with product and business stakeholders. I would love to discuss how this experience can help TomoCredit build robust APIs, scalable AWS-backed services, and reliable backend systems that help millions of users build credit and financial confidence. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

